<item>
            <title>[LU-19720] Implement renameat2() RENAME_WHITEOUT flag</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19720</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to have support for &lt;tt&gt;renameat2()&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s linux specific flags &lt;tt&gt;RENAME_WHITEOUT&lt;/tt&gt; so that Lustre could be safely used as a backend to some overlayfs implementations in user space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;WHITEOUT&lt;/tt&gt; directory entry is used to &quot;erase&quot; the presence of an identically-named entry in the underlying filesystem, so that it doesn&apos;t appear in ls/readdir output.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
